---
title: "GeometryChoice: How Calculators Record Decisions"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Calculator::Compute()
    participant F as KernelFilterSet
    participant B as GeometryChoiceBuilder
    participant GC as GeometryChoice
    participant PC as ProteinConformation
    participant UDP as OperationLog (UDP)

    C->>C: outer loop: for each target atom
    C->>C: inner loop: for each source (ring/bond/atom)

    C->>F: AcceptAll(context)
    alt Filter rejects
        F-->>C: false
        C->>F: LastRejectorName()
        F-->>C: "DipolarNearField"
        C->>B: Record(calculator, group, "exclusion", lambda)
        B->>GC: create choice
        Note over GC: AddAtom(target, Excluded)<br/>AddRing(source, Excluded)<br/>AddNumber("distance", 2.1, "A")<br/>filter_name = "DipolarNearField"
        B->>PC: append to geometry_choices
    else Filter accepts
        F-->>C: true
        C->>C: compute kernel T_ab = ...
        C->>C: accumulate on ConformationAtom
    end

    opt Triggered event (clamp, refinement)
        C->>B: Record(calculator, group, "E-field clamp", lambda)
        Note over GC: AddAtom(target, Triggered)<br/>AddNumber("E_mag", 142.0, "V/A")
        B->>PC: append to geometry_choices
    end

    C->>UDP: log filter statistics
    Note over UDP: streams to UI viewer<br/>for real-time visualisation
